{{title "Tinker"}}
<h1>Tinker Command</h1>
    
    {{ace-editor editorId="editor" resetEditorCallback=resetEditor text=model.text mode='html_ruby' editorChanged=(action 'editorChanged')}}

<div class="row">
    <div class="col col-xs-12">
        <div class="pull-right">
            {{#link-to 'home' class="btn btn-default"}}Cancel{{/link-to}}
            <button {{action 'save'}} class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
        </div>
        
        {{flash-messages}}
    </div>
</div>


<div class="panel panel-default">

    <div class="panel-body">
        <p>When you're finished - or if you get the code into a messed-up state - you can reset the tinker code back to its default.</p>
        <p>Be aware: This will erase any of your tinkering changes.  No other code will be affected.</p>

        <button {{action 'reset'}} class="btn btn-warning">Reset</button>
    </div>
</div>

{{outlet}}